memtrax_reaction_time.description: Reaction time for correct responses in cognitive task
memtrax_reaction_time.clinical_significance: Slower reaction times indicate cognitive decline
memtrax_reaction_time.transformation_notes: Convert milliseconds to seconds if needed

memtrax_accuracy.description: Percentage of correct responses in cognitive task
memtrax_accuracy.transformation_notes: Convert percentage to proportion if needed (divide by 100)

memtrax_total_responses.description: Total number of responses in the task
memtrax_total_responses.clinical_significance: Low response count may indicate engagement issues

ecog_self_total.clinical_significance: Higher scores indicate more self-reported cognitive problems
ecog_self_total.calculation: Sum of all ECOG self-report items
ecog_self_total.missing_value_handling: Require at least 80% completion for valid total

ecog_informant_total.description: Total ECOG score from informant report
ecog_informant_total.clinical_significance: Higher scores indicate more informant-reported cognitive problems
ecog_informant_total.calculation: Sum of all ECOG informant items

age.clinical_significance: Age is primary risk factor for cognitive decline

education.clinical_significance: Higher education associated with cognitive reserve

gender.clinical_significance: Gender differences in cognitive aging patterns

depression.clinical_significance: Can affect cognitive performance and self-awareness

ecog_completeness.description: Ensure ECOG questionnaires are sufficiently complete

ecog_discrepancy.description: Difference between informant and self ECOG scores

interpretation.positive: Informant reports more problems than participant
interpretation.negative: Participant reports more problems than informant

ecog_discrepancy.clinical_significance: Large positive discrepancy may indicate anosognosia

cognitive_efficiency.description: Combined measure of speed and accuracy
cognitive_efficiency.interpretation: Higher values indicate better cognitive efficiency

age_adjusted_rt.clinical_significance: Removes age-related slowing from RT measures

milliseconds_to_seconds.description: Convert millisecond reaction times to seconds

ecog_impairment.description: ECOG score cutoffs for impairment classification
